The order will have to go to the Constitutional Court so it can be studied before it&#8217;s referred to Parliament. CAPE TOWN In a landmark ruling, the Western Cape High Court has found it is legal for adults to use marijuana in private homes.The ruling was handed down on Friday. The order will have to go to the Constitutional Court so it can be studied before it s referred to Parliament.The court has allowed for the possession, cultivation and use dagga at home, for private use. It s also ruled that sections of the Drug Trafficking Act, as well as the Medicines Control Act needed to be amended.More to follow.